TypeSignature.Value: .class public auto ansi beforefieldinit ImageFile extends DocumentFormat.OpenXml.OpenXmlCompositeElement

summary.para: Image File.
This class is available in Office 2007 or above.
When the object is serialized out as xml, it's qualified name is v:image.

remarks.format:
## Remarks [!INCLUDE[openxmlnoticeiso](~/includes/openxmlnoticeiso.md)]
`image (Image File)`
This element is used to draw an image that has been loaded from an external source. There is an implied rectangle that is the same size as the image. Any stroke or fill is applied to this implied rectangle. The stroke is drawn on top of the image. The fill is behind the image and therefore only visible through transparent areas of the image. Image transparency is either encoded in the file or defined via a color value using the chromakey attribute. Unlike the imagedata element (§14.1.2.11), the image element does not have a parent element.
[*Example*:
```xml <v:image src="myimage.gif" style="position:relative;top:1;left:1;width:50;height:45" cropbottom="10%" gamma="0.5" gain="2"> </v:image> ```
